<subSubSection id="E7A2B298FFD4786B6FEE1A7DFE087D6A" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph id="AF07E113FFD4786B6FEE1A7DFE717835" blockId="33.[151,533,290,349]" box="[151,440,325,349]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
(
<figureCitation id="3783FD96FFD4786B6FE71A7DFECB7835" box="[158,258,325,349]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="44.[151,229,1945,1966]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,172,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-88@44.[197,1396,159,1930]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="PLATE 4. A–I. General habitus. (A) Dialodia longilobata, sp. nov.; (B) Dialodia bispinata, sp. nov.; (C) Dialodia bilongata, sp. nov.; (D) Dialodia brevisetacea, sp. nov.; (E) Dialodia aviculobata, sp. nov.; (F) Evansolidia setacea, sp. nov.; (G) Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov.; (H) Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov.; (I) Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Plate 4C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="3783FD96FFD4786B6E771A7DFE797835" box="[270,432,325,349]" captionStart="FIGURES 218–225" captionStartId="75.[151,257,1769,1790]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,193,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-67@75.[187,1400,169,1747]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURES 218–225. Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov. (218) male pygofer, lataeral view; (219) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (220) right style, lateral view; (221) right style, dorsal view; (222) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (223) aedeagus, dorsal view; (224) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (225) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs. 218–225</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF07E113FFD4786B6FEE1ABFFDBE78F6" blockId="33.[151,1436,390,1206]" box="[151,631,390,415]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="9DCC3D01FFD4786B6FEE1ABFFF3A78F7" bold="true" box="[151,243,391,415]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 7.60 mm; female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF07E113FFD4786B6FBE1A93FB4D7A42" blockId="33.[151,1436,390,1206]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="9DCC3D01FFD4786B6FBE1A93FE0578AB" bold="true" box="[199,460,427,451]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Medium size, robust species. General color black and yellow, forewings with yellow veins medially, cells translucent except distal ½ and apex of clavus; mesonotum mostly yellow with black triangulate marking on each side of middle below anterior margin, round black spot medially; pronotum with yellow broken band on anterior margin, yellow irregular shaped markings beneath anterior margin; crown yellow with broad, longitudinal stripes on each side of middle; eyes black; face yellow, clypeus with long broad reddish brown stripes laterally; clypellus reddish brown, bordered by black in distal half, long black irregular shaped stripe below eyes (
<figureCitation id="3783FD96FFD4786B6FE719BAFECA7BF2" box="[158,259,642,666]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="44.[151,229,1945,1966]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,172,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-88@44.[197,1396,159,1930]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="PLATE 4. A–I. General habitus. (A) Dialodia longilobata, sp. nov.; (B) Dialodia bispinata, sp. nov.; (C) Dialodia bilongata, sp. nov.; (D) Dialodia brevisetacea, sp. nov.; (E) Dialodia aviculobata, sp. nov.; (F) Evansolidia setacea, sp. nov.; (G) Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov.; (H) Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov.; (I) Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Plate 4C</figureCitation>
). Head narrower than prontum, anterior margin broadly rounded; crown broad, slightly narrower at base than width of eyes, produced distally about ¼ entire length, lateral margins convergent basally, disk elevated, slightly carinate, depressed on each side of middle; pronotum about as long as median length of crown, surface bullated; mesonotum large, about ½ times as long as pronotum; forewings typical; clypeus long, narrow, lateral margins broadly convex; clypellus narrow, base inflated, lateral margins constricted medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF07E113FFD4786B6FBE180FFE087D6A" blockId="33.[151,1436,390,1206]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="9DCC3D01FFD4786B6FBE180FFEB17A27" bold="true" box="[199,376,822,847]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view broad with small lobe on caudodorsal margin (
<figureCitation id="3783FD96FFD4786B6BEB180EFB3D7A26" box="[1170,1268,822,846]" captionStart="FIGURES 218–225" captionStartId="75.[151,257,1769,1790]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,193,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-67@75.[187,1400,169,1747]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURES 218–225. Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov. (218) male pygofer, lataeral view; (219) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (220) right style, lateral view; (221) right style, dorsal view; (222) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (223) aedeagus, dorsal view; (224) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (225) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 218</figureCitation>
); right subgenital plate long, narrow, glabrous (
<figureCitation id="3783FD96FFD4786B6D7E1862FDA07A1A" box="[519,617,858,882]" captionStart="FIGURES 218–225" captionStartId="75.[151,257,1769,1790]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,193,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-67@75.[187,1400,169,1747]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURES 218–225. Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov. (218) male pygofer, lataeral view; (219) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (220) right style, lateral view; (221) right style, dorsal view; (222) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (223) aedeagus, dorsal view; (224) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (225) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 219</figureCitation>
); style robust, shorter than aedeagus, large lateral subapical lobe in lateral view, apex slightly bifurcate (
<figureCitation id="3783FD96FFD4786B6E9A1846FD4E7AFE" box="[483,647,894,918]" captionStart="FIGURES 218–225" captionStartId="75.[151,257,1769,1790]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,193,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-67@75.[187,1400,169,1747]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURES 218–225. Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov. (218) male pygofer, lataeral view; (219) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (220) right style, lateral view; (221) right style, dorsal view; (222) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (223) aedeagus, dorsal view; (224) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (225) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs. 220, 221</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long, narrow, tubular except apically, lateral subapical lobe on lateral margin with numerous setae in dorsal view, gonopore medial (
<figureCitation id="3783FD96FFD4786B6CA7189AFB407AD2" box="[990,1161,930,954]" captionStart="FIGURES 218–225" captionStartId="75.[151,257,1769,1790]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,193,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-67@75.[187,1400,169,1747]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURES 218–225. Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov. (218) male pygofer, lataeral view; (219) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (220) right style, lateral view; (221) right style, dorsal view; (222) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (223) aedeagus, dorsal view; (224) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (225) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs. 222, 223</figureCitation>
); connective broadly Yshaped, membranous on each side of middle, stem very short (
<figureCitation id="3783FD96FFD4786B6C2D18FEFC7F7AB6" box="[852,950,966,990]" captionStart="FIGURES 218–225" captionStartId="75.[151,257,1769,1790]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,193,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-67@75.[187,1400,169,1747]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURES 218–225. Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov. (218) male pygofer, lataeral view; (219) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (220) right style, lateral view; (221) right style, dorsal view; (222) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (223) aedeagus, dorsal view; (224) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (225) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 224</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective long, narrow, gradually tapered distally (
<figureCitation id="3783FD96FFD4786B6E2B18D2FE7D7D6A" box="[338,436,1002,1026]" captionStart="FIGURES 218–225" captionStartId="75.[151,257,1769,1790]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,193,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-67@75.[187,1400,169,1747]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="FIGURES 218–225. Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov. (218) male pygofer, lataeral view; (219) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (220) right style, lateral view; (221) right style, dorsal view; (222) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (223) aedeagus, dorsal view; (224) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (225) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 225</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
